        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(agents): reuse media tool availability during tool prep",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Reuse the optional media tool factory plan for the image tool instead of resolving image availability separately.\n- Let image/video/music generation tool factories skip their registration-time availability scan when createOpenClawTools already resolved availability.\n- Use the same effective media tool config for the plan and constructed media tools.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior or issue addressed: Repeated warm `createOpenClawCodingTools` prep was spending about 29ms each registering `image_generate`, `video_generate`, and `music_generate` because those factories repeated availability checks already resolved by the OpenClaw media factory plan.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS, branch `media-tool-availability-pr4c`, Node 25.9.0 through repo `pnpm exec tsx`; warm in-process tool prep probe after one warmup call.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran a real local `node`/`tsx` probe that imports `createOpenClawCodingTools`, records `recordToolPrepStage` timings, discards one warmup call, then records 30 warm samples; wrapped with `/usr/bin/time -l`.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```text\ntotal p50 103.68ms, p95 110.16ms\nopenclaw-tools:image_generate registration p50 0.005ms\nopenclaw-tools:video_generate registration p50 0.002ms\nopenclaw-tools:music_generate registration p50 0.002ms\n/usr/bin/time -l max RSS 850575360 bytes\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: Single-call warm p50 improved by about 84ms versus the previous same-probe baseline, from 187.74ms p50 to 103.68ms p50 (~45%). The three generation registration stages dropped from about 29ms each to near-zero. Remaining warm prep cost is mostly plugin-tools (~73ms p50) and image/media availability planning (~30ms p50).\n\nWhat was not tested: Full end-to-end provider media generation was not run; this PR only changes registration-time availability reuse, while direct factory calls and execution-time provider resolution remain covered by targeted tests.\n\n## Verification\n- pnpm test src/agents/openclaw-tools.media-factory-plan.test.ts src/agents/tools/image-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/music-generate-tool.test.ts\n- pnpm tsgo:core\n- pnpm build\n- pnpm check:changed --staged",
